-- Version log entry for the bidirectional admin_users replication ship.
--
-- Run twice — once with :env='dev' against dev DB, once with :env='prod'
-- against prod RDS via superadmin temp creds.
--
-- Variables:
--   :env      → 'dev' or 'prod'
--   :version  → git short SHA shipped (7f98879)
--   :author   → Bryan's user id (super_admin)

INSERT INTO version_log (id, environment, entry_type, title, description, version, created_by)
VALUES (
    gen_random_uuid(),
    :env,
    'feature',
    'Bidirectional admin_users replication (dev <-> prod)',
    E'## What it does\n\nEvery admin_users mutation (CreateAdminUser, UpdateAdminRole, RemoveAdminRole, UpdateUserStatus, ResetUserPassword) now dual-writes to BOTH the local DB and a configured mirror DB. Pattern is synchronous "fail-loud":\n\n  1. BEGIN local tx\n  2. apply change to local (uncommitted)\n  3. apply change to mirror (autocommit)\n  4. mirror succeeds → commit local\n  5. mirror fails → rollback local, return error to caller\n\nReads always go to the local DB, so a mirror outage never blocks reads. At boot, when ADMIN_MIRROR_DB_DSN is set, a one-shot bidirectional UPSERT keyed by email reconciles any drift accumulated while the mirror was offline. Same-email-different-id conflicts resolve last-writer-wins by updated_at and are logged for an operator to review.\n\nThe createadmin CLI was refactored to go through the repository layer, so admin rows created from the CLI replicate immediately too.\n\n## Why\n\nJoe Workman''s partner account (joe@workmaninsurancegroup.com) existed only on dev. Without replication, every admin/support/marketing/partner account had to be created twice — once per env — and an account created in either env was invisible to the other. The post-00032 schema split made per-kind email uniqueness possible, but only if both envs see the same admin set.\n\n## Configuration\n\nGated by ADMIN_MIRROR_DB_DSN (libpq DSN). Unset → no replication, admin CRUD is local-only. Set → boot-sync + runtime dual-write turn on, all logged with [ADMIN-MIRROR] prefix.\n\n- Dev reads the var from /home/carecomp/carecompanion/.env. DSN points at prod RDS as the scoped role carecomp_admin_mirror (admin_users only — no PHI access).\n- Prod reads the var from AWS Secrets Manager (carecompanion/admin-mirror-dsn, ARN suffix P4oBfu), pulled in launch-template userdata and injected as a docker -e var. DSN points at admin EC2 private IP 10.0.1.129:5432 as carecomp_admin_mirror.\n\n## Networking\n\nSG ingress rule sgr-009f65c38467cb866 on sg-0a4d8f146c6b6de24 (carecompanion-dev-sg) authorizes 5432 from sg-0dcbf363b7127e05d (prod ASG SG). Same VPC so SG-reference works without peering. Auto-tracks ASG instance refreshes.\n\n## Scoped DB principal\n\ncarecomp_admin_mirror exists on both databases with identical password (file /home/carecomp/secrets/admin_mirror_db_pass.txt, mode 600). Grants: USAGE on schema public + SELECT/INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE on admin_users. Verified denied on app_users.\n\n## Verified paths (dev)\n\n- Boot sync: pushed joe@workmaninsurancegroup.com dev → prod (1/0/0) on the first restart with ADMIN_MIRROR_DB_DSN set.\n- Runtime dual-write: harness called CreateAdminUser → same UUID present on both sides immediately.\n- Failure rollback: harness with deliberately bad mirror pool → CreateAdminUser returned error AND local row count unchanged.\n\n## Failure modes\n\n- Mirror DB down at boot: pool init fails, app continues with replication OFF (fail-soft). Admin CRUD still works locally.\n- Mirror DB down at runtime: dual-write returns error to caller; local rolls back; admin user op fails loudly to operator.\n- Mirror commits then local fails (rare race): logged CRITICAL; orphan on mirror that next boot''s reconciliation surfaces and resolves last-writer-wins.\n\n## Infra changes shipped alongside this code\n\n- IAM: extended carecompanion-ec2-role inline policy SecretsAccess to include carecompanion/admin-mirror-dsn ARN.\n- Launch template: created lt-0de45f6f2603d93ed v16 (from v15), adding the secret pull and -e ADMIN_MIRROR_DB_DSN injection. ASG carecompanion-asg updated to use v16.\n- Security group: sgr-009f65c38467cb866 added (5432 from prod ASG SG to admin EC2 SG).\n- Secrets Manager: carecompanion/admin-mirror-dsn created (suffix P4oBfu).\n- Database principals: carecomp_admin_mirror role created on both dev docker-postgres and prod RDS, identical password.\n\n## Commits\n\n7f98879 feat(admin-replication): bidirectional admin_users dual-write across dev/prod',
    :version,
    :author
);
